OL,3,CEngland and penalty shootouts: Why is
OL,4,Cthere more confidence than ever?
OL,6,FAgainst Croatia, he initially used a
OL,7,Fstuttering run-up and saw his penalty
OL,8,Fsaved, although it had to be retaken
OL,9,Fafter the goalkeeper moved off his
OL,10,Fline. Kane converted the second
OL,11,Fattempt with a more conventional run-
OL,12,Fup.
OL,14,FResearch suggests the stuttering
OL,15,Ftechnique offers a slight advantage,
OL,16,Fwith a conversion rate of around 80%,
OL,17,Fcompared with 76% for a traditional
OL,18,Frun-up.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
